description: After a new air fryer recipe? This tasty teriyaki salmon recipe is easy to make and ready in 20 minutes. Dinner's done in a dash!
keywords: Fish dishes,Air fryer,Quick & easy dinner,High protein,Rice,Low sugar,Salmon
name: Air-Fryer Salmon With Teriyaki Glaze Recipe | Woolworths

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat air fryer to 200Â°C for 3 minutes. Place salmon in a shallow dish. Pour over sauce and turn to coat. Line air fryer basket with baking paper, trimming to fit. Using tongs, place salmon in paper-lined basket. Slide pan and basket into appliance. Set timer for 8 minutes. Cook, basting with any remaining sauce halfway through cooking time, or until cooked to your liking.
Meanwhile, heat rice according to packet instructions. Prepare salad according to kit instructions.

Transfer rice to a bowl. Stir in two-thirds of the sesame seeds. Divide rice mixture and salad among bowls. Top with salmon and any cooking juices. Serve scattered with onion and remaining sesame seeds.
